-- European Coal for 2013 Has Longest Run of Declines Since October
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-12-11T14:58:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-11/european-coal-for-2013-has-longest-run-of-declines-since-october.html
European coal for 2013 delivery
dropped for the sixth day, the longest run of declines in more
than a month.  Thermal coal for delivery next year to Amsterdam, Rotterdam
or Antwerp declined 0.4 percent to $95.10 a metric ton,
according to broker data compiled by Bloomberg. The sixth
straight drop marks the longest run since the period to Oct. 29.  Bloomberg tracks information from ICAP Plc, GFI Group Inc.,
Marex Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett Prebon Plc.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson at 
 lpaulsson@bloomberg.net  